{"id":101592,"date":"2019-09-27T14:24:08","date_gmt":"2019-09-27T14:24:08","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/?p=101592"},"modified":"2019-09-30T19:17:42","modified_gmt":"2019-09-30T19:17:42","slug":"industry-alert-brazilian-regulator-issues-warning-regarding-xm-global-limited","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/2019\/09\/27\/industry-alert-brazilian-regulator-issues-warning-regarding-xm-global-limited\/","title":{"rendered":"Industry News: Brazilian regulator issues warning regarding XM Global Limited","gt_translate_keys":[{"key":"rendered","format":"text"}]},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The Brazilian Securities Commission (CVM) published a <a href=\"http:\/\/sistemas.cvm.gov.br\/dados\/AtosDeclaratorios\/2C0216114DCE445185F737F00DB7EAC7.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">warning<\/a> on September 20th, 2019 regarding international broker XM Global Limited. The warning concerns offering Forex services to brazilian residents, which are currently banned under brazilian law.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-200 wp-image-101605\" src=\"https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-200x113.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"113\" srcset=\"https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-200x113.jpg 200w, https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-400x225.jpg 400w, https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-600x338.jpg 600w, https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675-800x450.jpg 800w, https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/09\/movingtoBrazil_0-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>The CVM has indicated that it will fine the company 1,000 reals ($239) per day if it does not cease offering it services to brazilian residents, although it is unclear how the CVM can accomplish this task.<\/p>\n<p>Such situations are becoming more frequent as regulatory requirements and restrictions take shape in developing countries. Brokers should be aware of all local and national restrictions in the regions they operate in.<\/p>\n<p>If you have concerns about the status of XM or another broker, visit our \u2018<a href=\"https:\/\/financialcommission.com.co\/check-your-broker\/\">Check Your Broker<\/a>\u2019 directory or email us at <a href=\"mailto:info@financialcommission.com.co\">info@financialcommission.com.co<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false,"gt_translate_keys":[{"key":"rendered","format":"html"}]},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The Brazilian Securities Commission (CVM) published a warning on September 20th, 2019 regarding international broker XM Global Limited. The warning concerns offering Forex services to brazilian residents, which are currently banned under brazilian law. The CVM has indicated that it will fine the company 1,000 reals ($239) per day if it does not cease offering [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false,"gt_translate_keys":[{"key":"rendered","format":"html"}]},"author":14,"featured_media":101593,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[54],"tags":[55,56,57,58,59,60,61,62,63,64,65,66,67,68,69,70,71,72,73,74,75],"class_list":["post-101592","post","type-post","status-publis